---
/**
 * rest-api · 0008 · Figure 1 — "Two gates, in order · AuthN vs AuthZ".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/rest-api/lessons/0008-authentication-and-authorization.html (figure + svg
 * + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the MDX, because
 * MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses kebab-case attrs
 * (text-anchor, font-size, stroke-width, marker-end, …).
 *
 * The source defines its arrow markers ONCE in a top-level <svg><defs> in <body>
 * and the figures reference them via url(#arw). To keep each extracted figure
 * SELF-CONTAINED, the markers it references are inlined here in its own <defs>,
 * with the SAME ids and fills as the source so the rendering is byte-identical.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 188"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Authentication asks who are you and fails with 401; authorization asks what may you do and fails with 403"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
            >
                <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path>
            </marker>
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">TWO GATES, IN ORDER · DIFFERENT FAILURES</text
            >
            <rect
                x="14"
                y="34"
                width="290"
                height="120"
                rx="10"
                fill="#eef2f5"
                stroke="#1f3a5a"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="159"
                y="56"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">① AUTHENTICATION</text
            >
            <text
                x="159"
                y="76"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-style="italic"
                fill="#1f3a5a">who are you?</text
            >
            <text x="159" y="98" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >prove identity from a credential</text
            >
            <rect x="46" y="112" width="226" height="30" rx="7" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="159"
                y="131"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">missing / invalid → 401 Unauthorized</text
            >
            <line x1="304" y1="94" x2="336" y2="94" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <text x="320" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">pass</text>
            <rect
                x="336"
                y="34"
                width="290"
                height="120"
                rx="10"
                fill="#eef5ee"
                stroke="#2f5d3a"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="481"
                y="56"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">② AUTHORIZATION</text
            >
            <text
                x="481"
                y="76"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-style="italic"
                fill="#2f5d3a">what may you do?</text
            >
            <text x="481" y="98" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >may this principal do this, here?</text
            >
            <rect x="368" y="112" width="226" height="30" rx="7" fill="#f7ecea" stroke="#9a2417"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="481"
                y="131"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#9a2417">known but not allowed → 403 Forbidden</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="178" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#7a1f12"
                >A request can pass gate ① and fail gate ② on the very next line — the priciest bugs
                live in that gap.</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        <strong>401</strong> = come back with valid identity; <strong>403</strong> = your identity is
        fine, the answer is still no. (401 is a misnomer; it means <em>unauthenticated</em>.)
    </figcaption>
</figure>
